fields.description:
When attempting to add an email address that is already in use by another user or account, the error is

{{user@domain.com is not available.}}

This should probably be something like

{{user@domain.com is in use by another account.}}

In a README.md for one of our repositories (it is private, unfortunately), there is a link to this URL:

{code}
http://wiki.ourteamname.com/ourproject:somepage
{code}

However, this URL is rendered by BitBucket:

{code}
https://bitbucket.org/ourteamname/ourproject
{code}

Not sure why, maybe because of the colon? All other links in our README.md are rendered correctly.

Three braces should generate preformatted element, but:

{{{\\
is it pre?\\
is it pre?\\
is it pre?\\
}}}
